title: Timing of King's climate remarks in France felt awkward - as UK government delays targets
description: Two busy days, but job done for the King and Queen in Paris.

title: Devious parasitic plant convinces host to grow into its own flesh
description: Scientists have observed how a merciless parasitic plant convinces its host to grow into its own flesh.

title: TikTok star jailed after saying Islamic prayer before eating pork in viral video
description: A woman in Indonesia has been jailed for two years after saying an Islamic prayer before eating pork in a viral TikTok video.

title: Three navy personnel die after being swept off submarine deck
description: Three South African navy personnel have died after seven members of a submarine crew were swept off the vessel's deck by large waves, the country's department of defence has said.

title: Rupert Murdoch stepping down as chair of Fox and News Corp
description: Rupert Murdoch is stepping down as chair of Fox and News Corp.

title: Five people suspected of spying for Russia to be charged with espionage offence, CPS says
description: Five people suspected of spying for Russia are to be charged with conspiracy to conduct espionage, the Crown Prosecution Service has said.

title: In pictures: King gifted football shirt and Queen plays table tennis on tour of Paris
description: The King received a warm welcome from French politicians while he delivered a historic speech as the first British monarch to speak at the country's senate.

title: Saudi prince says he will continue 'sportswashing' to boost economy
description: Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman has said he "doesn't care" if Saudi Arabia is accused of "sportswashing" - as long as it adds to the country's GDP.

title: Canada shifting diplomats in India amid 'threats' - as visas suspended for its citizens
description: Canada is "adjusting" its diplomatic staff presence in India as the South Asian nation suspended visas for Canadian citizens, widening a rift between the two countries.

title: Ryanair criticises airport after passenger in wheelchair left behind
description: Ryanair has criticised a French airport after a plane bound for Scotland was forced to U-turn on the runway after it was discovered a passenger in a wheelchair had been left behind.

title: King Charles says UK will 'always be one of France's closest allies and best friends' in historic speech
description: The King has said the late Queen's "golden thread will forever shine brightly" in the first ever speech by a British monarch to the French Senate.

title: 'Every day we get closer': Bin Salman suggests Saudi Arabia and Israel are set to reach historic deal
description: The Crown Prince of Saudi Arabia, Mohammed Bin Salman, has denied reports that negotiations with Israel over a possible normalisation deal have been suspended and insisted that "every day we get closer".

title: Poland to stop giving Ukraine weapons as grain row escalates
description: Poland will stop supplying weapons to Ukraine after a row about grain imports saw President Volodymyr Zelenskyy criticise the country at the UN and Warsaw summon Kyiv's ambassador.

title: New virus discovered in Pacific is deepest ever found in Earth's oceans
description: A new virus discovered in the Pacific is thought to be the deepest ever found in Earth's oceans.

title: Troubled electronics and energy giant Toshiba to leave stock market after more than 70 years
description: Troubled electronics and energy giant Toshiba is set to become a private company after more than 70 years on the stock market.

title: Sponsor an ocean - tiny Pacific island comes up with novel way to protect waters
description: The tiny Pacific island nation of Niue has come up with a novel way to protect its waters from illegal fishing and plastic waste - it will ask people to sponsor parts of its ocean.

title: Iran's president warns Saudi Arabia not to make peace with Israel
description: Iran's president is warning Saudi Arabia against making peace with Israel.
